Rating: 4
Great tapas or appetizer with a crusty bread. Use a really good sherry and your favorite flavorful ham. Be careful not to overcook the garlic slices and use the proportions described in the recipe to get the right sauce consistency. I have served this many times as an appetizer and in a pinch, as a fast Friday night dinner with a good Spanish white wine and a side salad. It's a keeper.

Rating: 4
truly fabulous when made properly perfect the first time I made it, not so good the second, when I overcooked the garlic (became bitter) and used a not great sherry. a good way to use the leftovers from the holiday ham

