Rating: 4
This recipe was a huge hit at my Christmas dinner. Kids and adults alike. The garlic is not overpowering, the ham is a nice contrast to the shrimp. The presentation is gorgeous ( I plated it) This is a must for those who love shrimp and a great introduction to those who have only had shrimp cocktail. Wonderful and Yummy!

Rating: 4
Seldom do I give a four fork rating, but this was delicious. I served it over rice as a main dish for my husband and myself. I dressed the rice up with a couple of tablespoons of sherry vinegar boiled with sugar, then stirred into the finished rice. This gave a little more interest to the rice and went well with the shrimp/ham dish.

Rating: 4
Superb recipe! I usually only rate items that are really good (or really bad...as a warning!), and this dish is awesome. Made it last night with the Pork Empanadas (also highly recommend!) from this site, and dinner was fantastic! Definately use a Spanish cream sherry for this, as it really enhances the flavor of the shrimp.

Rating: 4
